
=More information=

Table 2 shows the data corresponding to Methods B, between 2000 and 2013. These data are identifiable in the dataset and/or are reported in the national methodological reports (NMRs). The common land area can be identified in the data only when corresponding to Method B option 2 or Method B option 3. Common land assigned to agricultural holdings (Method B option 1) cannot be identified. Even when common land units record land other than UAA, only the land which is part of UAA is reported as common land in Table 2 (in line with the definition of common land)."
 
